<p><b>Alfred Elton van Vogt</b> (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1912-04-26"><a href="/wiki/April_26" title="April 26">26 April</a> <a href="/wiki/1912" title="1912">1912</a></span> – <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2000-01-26"><a href="/wiki/January_26" title="January 26">26 January</a> <a href="/wiki/2000" title="2000">2000</a></span>) was a <a href="/wiki/Canada" title="Canada">Canadian</a>-born <a href="/wiki/Science_fiction_author" title="Science fiction author" class="mw-redirect">science fiction author</a> who was one of the most prolific and complex<sup class="noprint Template-Fact"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources&#160;since March 2009" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</span></sup> writers of the mid-twentieth century "<a href="/wiki/Golden_Age_of_Science_Fiction" title="Golden Age of Science Fiction">Golden Age</a>" of the genre.</p>
