<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> For example, Peter Nicholls (<cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREF.5B.5BJohn_Clute.7CClute.2C_John.5D.5D_.26_.5B.5BPeter_Nicholls.7CNicholls.2C_Peter.5D.5D"><a href="/wiki/John_Clute" title="John Clute">Clute, John</a> &amp; <a href="/wiki/Peter_Nicholls" title="Peter Nicholls">Nicholls, Peter</a>, ed. <i>The Encyclopedia of Science Fiction</i>. New York: <a href="/wiki/St._Martin%27s_Press" title="St. Martin's Press">St. Martin's Press, Inc.</a>. p.&#160;199. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0312096186" class="internal">ISBN 0-312-09618-6</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Encyclopedia+of+Science+Fiction&amp;rft.pages=p.%26nbsp%3B199&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BSt.+Martin%27s+Press%7CSt.+Martin%27s+Press%2C+Inc.%5D%5D&amp;rft.isbn=0-312-09618-6&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:A._E._van_Vogt"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>) says "The beginning of Campbell's particular Golden Age of SF can be pinpointed as the summer of 1939," and goes on to begin the discussion with the July 1939 issue. Lester del Rey (<cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFdel_Rey1979"><a href="/wiki/Lester_del_Rey" title="Lester del Rey">del Rey, Lester</a> (1979). <i>The World of Science Fiction and Fantasy: The History of a Subculture</i>. New York: Ballantine Books. p.&#160;94. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/034525452X" class="internal">ISBN 0-345-25452-X</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+World+of+Science+Fiction+and+Fantasy%3A+The+History+of+a+Subculture&amp;rft.aulast=del+Rey&amp;rft.aufirst=Lester&amp;rft.au=del+Rey%2C+Lester&amp;rft.date=1979&amp;rft.pages=p.%26nbsp%3B94&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Ballantine+Books&amp;